+text

-text


Addendum 4384-2:** The following is an excerpted experimental log involving SCP-4384. The trials were conducted on ██/██/20██ by Dr. Roe to deduce different reactions of SCP-4384 from stimuli.


Stimulus
Test Results


Common rabbit introduced into the enclosure.
SCP-4384 shows no signs of interest, watching subject for a few moments before perching atop a branch.


Instance of Thamnophis sirtalis sirtalis (Eastern garter snake) introduced into the enclosure.
SCP-4384 shows no signs of interest, proceeding to preen itself for several minutes until the conclusion of the test.


Instance of Cerastes cerastes (Desert Horned Viper) introduced into the enclosure.
SCP-4384 becomes exceptionally hostile, producing shrieks of over 180-decibels and attempting to claw at the snake with its talons.1


D-201512 instructed to enter the enclosure.
SCP-4384 produces a shrill emission, causing temporary deafness in D-20151.


D-21867 instructed to enter enclosure, bearing a mask of Haida make, similar to the one discovered with SCP-4384.
SCP-4384 remains silent for several moments, before cautiously flying near D-21867. After a short period of examination, SCP-4384 returns to its perch, showing no additional signs of interest.


Dr. Roe3 instructed to enter the enclosure.
SCP-4384 immediately becomes curious, flying towards Dr. Roe before promptly perching on her shoulder. SCP-4384 later returns to roost on top of one of the aviary mews.


A recording of a red-tailed hawk shriek is played.
SCP-4384 produces a mating call commonly associated with male instances of Buteo Jamaicensis and ruffles its feathers. It prepares to lift off from its perch, but then pauses and quickly folds its wings. SCP-4384 makes no additional response to repeat playing of the recording.






Footnotes
1. Despite intense efforts, SCP-4384 was unable to harm the subject other than temporarily disorienting it.
2. Note: D-20151 was convicted for various charges of arson and manslaughter.
3. Part of the SCP-4384 containment team, selected for participation based on background in veterinary biology and commendations for exemplary employee behavior.






